You are building an Excel workbook (.xlsx) for storm sewer data entry that feeds into Hydraflow Storm Sewers Extension via CSV export. The workbook has two sheets: Lines and Inlets. It must be built with openpyxl.

GENERAL RULES

All column headers must exactly match the names listed below — these are parsed by a Python script that uses them as keys.
No commas or quotation marks are allowed in any text input cell. Add a note or comment on the Line ID and Inlet ID cells stating this.
Read-only/reference columns are filled with a medium grey fill (D9D9D9) and have sheet protection applied so they cannot be edited.
Editable columns have a white or light blue fill (EBF4FF) and are unlocked.
Each sheet is protected (password optional, your choice), with only unlocked cells editable.
Row 1 is a frozen, bold header row on both sheets.
Provide 25 blank data rows below the header on each sheet (rows 2–26), pre-formatted with all fills, dropdowns, and conditional formatting applied.
Column widths should be set to fit the header text comfortably.

DEFAULTS SECTION (Both Sheets)
At the top of each sheet, insert a Defaults band above the main data table:

Row 1: A merged cell across all columns labeled "DEFAULT VALUES" — bold, white text on a dark blue background (1F3864).
Row 2: One input cell per editable column, aligned to match the column position of the main table below. These cells are filled yellow (FFFACD) and unlocked. Leave read-only columns empty/grey in this row.
Row 3: Main table header row (bold, dark blue background, white text).
Rows 4–28: 25 data rows.

The yellow default cells in row 2 accept the same input types and dropdown lists as the corresponding data column below them. A user fills in whichever defaults they want, and the Python importer reads row 2 before reading the data rows — any data cell left blank in the table will be back-filled with the corresponding default value from row 2 during the merge. If a data cell has a value, it takes priority over the default.
Add a note on the merged row 1 cell stating: "Fill yellow cells to set defaults. Blank cells in the table below will inherit the default value during import. Individual row values always take priority."

