ADDITIONAL NOTES

The Location field (Inlets col D) should also show a note that Drop Curb inlets are always assumed to be in a sag by Hydraflow — the Location field is not required for them.
The Generic Capac. field should have a note: "WARNING: Generic inlets should not be used in sags when capacity < total Q."
The Line Slope field should have a note: "If Invert Dn and Invert Up are both entered, slope is auto-calculated by the importer. Enter a slope here only if you want to override the upstream invert."
The Inlets sheet is parallel to the Lines sheet — it has one row per line number, in the same order. Line No. (col A) on the Inlets sheet must match Line No. on the Lines sheet row-for-row. Pre-populate the Line No. column in rows 4–28 with the formula =Lines!A4 (and so on down) so they stay synchronized automatically. This column is read-only (grey fill, locked).
Not every line will have meaningful inlet data. For lines that don't have an inlet (e.g. a manhole-only junction), the user simply leaves those editable cells blank — the importer will treat blank as zero or preserve the original .stm value per the whitelist rules.
Do not allow the Inlets sheet to have a different number of rows than the Lines sheet, and do not allow Line No. to be manually typed. It must always mirror the Lines sheet.
Use openpyxl. Do not use xlwings or win32com.
